manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Real-time Tracking Anywhere and Anytime With SinoTrack gps tracker device, easily to check your cars, teenagers, workers in real time. Connecting device to your car and know your cars real-time location, trip histories, driving habits, etc. The ST-906L GPS location tracker use about 30MB data per month. It built-in 180mAh backup battery, When the engine starts will charging. Or you can connect it to your car battery directly, it will always online no worry outage. The ST-906L 4G gps tracker is compatible with any Smartphone, tablet, computer, iPad, etc. You can login to your account and track the car on Google maps via our free tracking platform anytime and anywhere. Never worry where your car, teenager or loved ones are. It can monitor if they’re safe.

Cut Engine Remotely This 4G gps tracker include relay, when you found your car was stolen, you can control your car remotely on your phone, cut the engine by sending SMS command, the vehicle will stop move until it received your SMS command “9400000”, prevent theft of your car on the parking lot.(The car will stop within 10-20sec when it get sms command) Attention：Only the car running below to 20KM/h,your car can stop when it get text command within a few sec. If the car running more than 20km/h,then your engine can't cut off.

More Detailes Dim 3.94*1.97*0.98 inch Weight 75g Band LTE-FDD B1/B2/B3/B4/B5/B7/B8/B28/B66 GSM 850/900/1800/1900MHz GPS Chip A7670SA GPS Sensitivity -162Db GPS Accuracy 5-10M Time to First Fix Cold status 45s;Warm status 35s;Hot status 1s Work Voltage 9v-60v Storage Temp -40℃ Packing list 1*ST-906L GPS tracker;1*Power cable;1*SOS Alarm Key;1*Locker Relay;1*MIC Wire;1*Sticker;1*Original Box

With Voice Monitor Car GPS tracker with voice Monitor, the sound around the tracker can be heard on your cell phone. When your car or love ones under the abnormal condition,send sms 66 to the control number ,The tracker will call back to this control number. If you make call the SIM number in the device,it will pick up your call automactically and you will can monitor the voice around the device.(Attention: You need to set control number for the tracker,so that you can use this function)

HOW TO QUICKLY SETTING UP THE TRACKER?STEP 1. – Activate Sim Buy a local SIM card with 2G(GSM) or 4G network function and Install the new sim card into your mobile phone and activate the sim card and remove SIM card’s PIN code. Make sure it can make a call, send a text and has an internet connection. Once this is confirmed, insert SIM to your tracker. STEP 2. – Turn on the tracker Charge it about 1 hour first. The yellow and blue indicator lights will start flashing while it searches for a network and GPS. Please wait 5 minutes in a good reception area (by a window or outside) for both lights to come on constantly. It will continue to flash yellow if it can not find a network. Move it to another location. Please note, when the device has a GPS signal it will get a GPS location. If not it will get its location using LBS. STEP 3. - Setting APN for the tracker (1) You need to know your tracker’s SIM card's APN (You can ask your SIM card provider); (2) Please note the following operations need From another phone number send text messages command to the tracker’s sim card’s phone number to set tracker's APN. For example: APN is: everywhere APN username is: eesecure APN password is: secure (1) If your SIM card’s APN without username and password, then send text command(8030000+space+APN) to the tracker, it will reply “SET OK”. Text command is: 8030000 everywhere (2) If your APN with username and password: Then sned text Command(8030000+Space+ APN+space+ APN user+Space+ APN pass) to the tracker : 8030000 everywhere eesecure secure Please note: Different SIM card has difference APN. Please apply the above formula according to your actual APN to set up your machine STEP 4. - Setting GPRS mode Send text command to the device to set GPRS mode:7100000 Then wait about 30sec, both blue and orange light should stay ON which mean you can now login to sinotrackpro web or app to check if tracker active. (Username is your tracker’s ID number that write on the product, password: 123456) If you set ok of all, you can track it online. If it online but show China location, then take it to the outside which signal good place to get GPRS signal, when it get signal, will update your location. If the device is not online, please check device setting, send: RCONF to device, It will reply the setting you can check in reply: 1. The APN if is correct; 2. The IP and Port if is correct(IP and port are write in the usermanual,you can check if same as reply) 3. The device working model, (GPRS model)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Worst support ever
reviews.reviewText: Bought my first sinotrack back in 2020. But the one i got is only 3g. Back then the support was very helpful and friendly. He walked me through every step very patiently. Unfortunately the tmobile stopped the 3g network so i have no choice but to get the 4glte version. I liked it thats why i got the new version last month. Setting up was easy like before and i was surprised how fast it is and very stable connection. But i ran into some issues with some features. The shake alarm, acc alarm, sos is not working. So i contacted support for some help. first it wont accept control number (my phone number) I got it figured out myself and now the features. I explained to her what was the issue. And i sent her the RCONF for her to see. I guess she didnt pay attention and asked to send it so i told her i already send it but i sent it again. Never got any solution from her she only reply with another question once a day and asked me to do things i already done. Then finally she got upset and told me that i was asking too many questions and she got confused. So i made it easier and told her that shake alarm is not working but the Rconf shows its on. Then she never replied anymore. She’s igoring me. Now the device keeps sending me sms and a phone call from sos alarm. Im getting shake alarm now but only when ita moving and acc on. Sos keeps sending every 10 mins 24/7. After a few search online and patience, i managed to figure out. Now i got it under control without the help of support. Manual is lacking information. I got some features turned on its not even in the manual. Its really a good device but a lot of missing information in the manual. And support is the worst. Rude and unhelpful. So i dont recommend this tracker anymore because of tech support. Good product bad customer service.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 7, 2022
reviews.reviewText: AT&T recently disabled 3G service and left my old tracker worthless. I was leary because this looks exactly the same as my 3G tracker but to my surprise it works on the 4G network. It is very easy to use and the only monthly fee is what ever you pay for the cell service through your provider. I don't use mine through the app but rather through text messages. I simply call the number and it responds with a text with its location on a Google map link. Very easy to install and use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 15, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for something that I can add to remote killswitch with tracking in my older car. Didn't want to use a physical toggle switch. This did the job.Once setup, it works great. First one I got, the killswitch on the app worked backwards. Exchanged for another one and it's working correctly.You can't change the system(kph to mph). Shouldn't really be an issue as I'm only using it for tracking and killswitch. But it would be nice to be able too.Also nice to be able to use different mobile SIM.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 8, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great purchase with constant updates for tracking
reviews.reviewText: So far, this has been a great purchase. I also ordered the hardwire kit (routed through my ACC fuse so it powers/charges it only when the key is engaged/engine is on). Tracking has been pretty darn accurate providing a detailed history of movement and the fee was a flat $19.95 with (I'd guess, based on what I see) 10 second interval updates.
